b'[<p><i><b>UFC on Fox: dos Santos vs. Miocic</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC on Fox 13</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held at <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/U.S._Airways_Center" title="U.S. Airways Center">U.S. Airways Center</a> in <a href="/wiki/Phoenix,_Arizona" title="Phoenix, Arizona">Phoenix</a>, <a href="/wiki/Arizona" title="Arizona">Arizona</a>, on December 13, 2014.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FoxPhoenix_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-FoxPhoenix-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The event was the first that the organization has hosted in Arizona. <a href="/wiki/Zuffa" title="Zuffa">Zuffa</a> previously hosted the final <a href="/wiki/World_Extreme_Cagefighting" title="World Extreme Cagefighting">World Extreme Cagefighting</a> event, <a href="/wiki/WEC_53" title="WEC 53">WEC 53</a>, in nearby <a href="/wiki/Glendale,_Arizona" title="Glendale, Arizona">Glendale</a> in 2010.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FoxPhoenix_2-1"><a href="#cite_note-FoxPhoenix-2">[2]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The fight card was headlined by a heavyweight bout between <a href="/wiki/Junior_dos_Santos" title="Junior dos Santos">Junior dos Santos</a> and <a href="/wiki/Stipe_Miocic" title="Stipe Miocic">Stipe Miocic</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Jussier_Formiga" title="Jussier Formiga">Jussier Formiga</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/John_Moraga" title="John Moraga">John Moraga</a> at the event. However, Formiga was forced to pull out of the fight due to injury and was replaced by UFC newcomer <a href="/wiki/Willie_Gates" title="Willie Gates">Willie Gates</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Nate_Diaz" title="Nate Diaz">Nate Diaz</a> missed weight on his first attempt at the weigh-ins, weighing in at 160.6 pounds. He was given additional time to make the lightweight limit, but made no attempt to cut further. Instead, he was fined 20 percent of his purse, which went to <a href="/wiki/Rafael_dos_Anjos" title="Rafael dos Anjos">Rafael dos Anjos</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>A middleweight bout between <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Ed_Herman_(mixed_martial_artist)" title="Ed Herman (mixed martial artist)">Ed Herman</a> and <a href="/wiki/Derek_Brunson" title="Derek Brunson">Derek Brunson</a>, slated for the televised preliminary portion of the event, was cancelled on the day of the event, as Brunson was stricken with a stomach ailment.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup> The fight was rescheduled to take place the following month at <a href="/wiki/UFC_183" title="UFC 183">UFC 183</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-HermanBrunson_8-0"><a href="#cite_note-HermanBrunson-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-10"><a href="#cite_note-10">[9]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses:<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[10]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following is the reported payout to the fighters as reported to the Arizona Boxing and MMA Commission. It does not include sponsor money and also does not include the UFC\'s traditional "fight night" bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-payouts_12-0"><a href="#cite_note-payouts-12">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>^ <i>Diaz was fined $4,000, 20 percent of his purse for failing to make the required weight for his fight with Rafael dos Anjos.  That money was issued to Dos Anjos, officials confirmed.</i><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-payouts_12-1"><a href="#cite_note-payouts-12">[11]</a></sup><br/>\n&lt; <i>Bout did not take place as Brunson was unable to compete after becoming ill the day of the fight.  Herman was paid his show money.</i><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-payouts_12-2"><a href="#cite_note-payouts-12">[11]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><br/>\n</p>]'